  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some AngularJS interview questions?",
  "response": "When preparing for an AngularJS interview, it's important to cover a range of topics, including core concepts, directives, services, controllers, and general best practices. Here are some common AngularJS interview questions:\n\n### Basic Questions:\n1. **What is AngularJS?**\n   - Explain what AngularJS is and its purpose as a framework.\n\n2. **What are the main features of AngularJS?**\n   - Discuss features such as two-way data binding, dependency injection, directives, etc.\n\n3. **What is a Module in AngularJS?**\n   - Define what a module is and how it is used in organizing an AngularJS application.\n\n4. **What is a Controller in AngularJS?**\n   - Describe the role of controllers in managing the application state and how they interact with views.\n\n5. **What is a Scope in AngularJS?**\n   - Explain the scope object and its importance in the two-way data binding mechanism.\n\n### Intermediate Questions:\n6. **What are Directives in AngularJS?**\n   - Describe what directives are and give examples (e.g., built-in directives like `ng-model`, custom directives).\n\n7. **How does Two-way Data Binding work in AngularJS?**\n   - Explain the concept of two-way data binding and how it is achieved in AngularJS.\n\n8. **What are Services in AngularJS?**\n   - Discuss the role of services in sharing code and logic across different parts of an application.\n\n9. **What is Dependency Injection in AngularJS?**\n   - Explain how dependency injection works in AngularJS and why it is beneficial.\n\n10. **What is the purpose of `$http` service?**\n    - Discuss how the `$http` service works for making AJAX requests and handling responses.\n\n### Advanced Questions:\n11. **What are Filters in AngularJS?**\n    - Describe what filters do and provide examples of built-in filters.\n\n12. **What is a Promise, and how is it used in AngularJS?**\n    - Explain the concept of promises and how they are used to handle asynchronous operations.\n\n13. **How do you handle routing in AngularJS?**\n    - Discuss the role ofngRoute and how to configure routes in an AngularJS application.\n\n14. **What is the digest cycle in AngularJS?**\n    - Explain how AngularJS detects changes and updates the view through the digest cycle.\n\n15. **What are some common performance issues in AngularJS applications?**\n    - Discuss potential performance bottlenecks and how to optimize AngularJS applications.\n\n### Practical Questions:\n16. **Can you demonstrate how to create a custom directive?**\n    - Provide an example of a simple custom directive and explain its purpose.\n\n17. **How would you implement form validation in AngularJS?**\n    - Describe the built-in validation features and how to create custom validations.\n\n18. **How can you create a single-page application (SPA) using AngularJS?**\n    - Discuss the structure of an SPA and how AngularJS helps in achieving this.\n\n19. **What are some best practices for structuring an AngularJS application?**\n    - Share recommendations on organizing files, using modules, and maintaining readability.\n\n20. **How do you test AngularJS applications?**\n    - Explain tools and frameworks that you can use for testing AngularJS applications, such as Jasmine and Protractor.\n\n### Conclusion:\nThese questions should give you a good foundation for understanding AngularJS concepts and prepare you for an interview. Be ready not only to answer but also to provide examples or demonstrations of your work where applicable.",
